-- TransCentury Plans to Trade on Nairobi's Exchange, Business Daily Reports
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2011-02-09T05:15:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/transcentury-plans-to-trade-on-nairobi-s-exchange-business-daily-reports.html
TransCentury Ltd., a Kenyan  investment company , plans to start trading its shares on the  Nairobi Stock Exchange  by the end of this year through
introduction, Business Daily reported today.  Shareholders of the investment club founded in 1998
yesterday approved an increase in share capital to 300 million
shillings ($3.7 million) from 200 million shillings by
increasing the number of shares to 600 million from 400 million,
Nairobi-based Business Daily said, citing proceedings at a
shareholders’ meeting.  TransCentury’s investment portfolio includes East African
Cables Ltd., Equity Bank Ltd., Kenya Airways Ltd. and Rift
Valley Railways, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  